\boxed{\alpha\text{-haloketones}}

**Explanation:** α-Haloketones (e.g., chloroacetone) undergo intramolecular nucleophilic substitution with aqueous base to form a **cyclopropanone intermediate**, which then rearranges (via ring-opening) to yield a carboxylic acid. This is a classic example of the **haloform-like rearrangement** or **α-haloketone cyclopropanone pathway**. The reaction is favored when the halogen is at the α-position relative to the carbonyl.
